{"title":"Ron’s Bikes CR1 Country Road Mid Reach Road Frame Pre-Order","link":"https://theradavist.com/rons-bikes-cr1-country-road-mid-reach-road-frame/","date":1741101165000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>Compact, modern, mid-reach, and all-steel, the CR1 or “Country Road” 1 is the latest from the mind of Ronnie Romance’s <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/rons-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Ron’s Bikes</a> brand. Made in Deep River, CT, by Darren Larkin of <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/larkin-cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Larkin Cycles</a> in the heart of Nutmeg Country, this chubby road bike clears a 700 by 39 mm tire, thanks to its incorporation of mid-reach calipers…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-05.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-05.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-06.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-06.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-06.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-06.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>CR1 Country Road Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>27.2 seatpost</li>\n<li>Two color options, TBD, plus raw.</li>\n<li><strong>$2,200 powder</strong> and <strong>$2,050 raw</strong></li>\n<li>1 1/8″ straight head tube</li>\n<li>68 mm English BB shell</li>\n<li>29-30.0 seatpost and front derailleur clamp</li>\n<li>Clearance for up to 700×39 tires</li>\n<li>Production will have downtube shifter stops</li>\n<li>External cable routing</li>\n<li>No fender mounts, no rack mounts</li>\n<li>130 rear spacing 100 front</li>\n<li>Pump peg for full-length frame pump</li>\n<li>2 water bottle cages</li>\n<li>Columbus tubing</li>\n<li>Made in Deep River, CT</li>\n<li>Lead time after pre-order closes 4-6 months.</li>\n<li>Deposit taken now, the rest due at shipping.</li>\n<li>FIT available in 5 sizes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-02.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-02.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/CR1_rons_bikes_mid_reach_road_geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/CR1_rons_bikes_mid_reach_road_geo.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/CR1_rons_bikes_mid_reach_road_geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/CR1_rons_bikes_mid_reach_road_geo.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n<p>This is a compact, or “sloping geo,” so to find your appropriate size, look at the top tube length, which will be on the slightly longer side – up to 4 cm – with a shorter stem.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-03.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-03.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-04.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-04.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-04.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Rons-Bikes-Mid-Reach-Road-04.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>There are several mid-reach caliper brakes out there from which to choose. The <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/TRP-RDR91320-Parent-RG957-Bike-Brake/dp/B00JNAEOWI?th=1\">TRP RG957</a> are really nice and clear the 700×39, also the Shimano BR R600, along with the <a href=\"https://velo-orange.com/products/grand-cru-long-reach-brakes\">VO grand cru brakes</a>. Regarding spec, you are looking for 47-57 mm of arm reach.</p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://ronsbikesblog.com/2025/03/01/rons-bikes-cr1-country-road-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Ron’s Bikes Blog</a> and hand over your $1,000 at <a href=\"https://ronsbikes.com/products/mid-reach-road-bike\" target=\"_blank\">Ron’s Bikes Webshop for the pre-order</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/rons-bikes-cr1-country-road-mid-reach-road-frame/\">Ron’s Bikes CR1 Country Road Mid Reach Road Frame Pre-Order</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"8233f57660e6dac06764647898869bdcebc783141e3994591238c7cd9bcf7b87","category":"Cycling"}